Grats Silinius on: <br>
 <img src="http://www.furysedge.com/news/030904/Tallonmantle.jpg" style="border:0;" ><br>
<br>
Oh yeah, we made an attempt on Vallon. We actually got him to 7% but no one out of the 72 man raid managed to get a screenshot of it. Lets just say we turned on our zerg switch toward the end of this one <br>
 <img src="http://www.malignwarlock.com/eq/burnarseoff.jpg" style="border:0;" ><br>
 <img src="http://www.malignwarlock.com/eq/burnhim.jpg" style="border:0;" ><br>

 <img src="http://www.furysedge.com/news/030904/vallon.jpg" style="border:0;" ><br>
<br>
<br>
Now, I would like to take this time to educate you all on the &quot;correct&quot; way to request items from your local Fury's Edge Magician's Union (FEMU) member. <br>
<br>
We Magicians do not like tells that are demanding and make us feel like we are being used and abused. Some examples of these kinds of tells are &quot;Rod&quot; or &quot;Bracer bitch&quot;, I've even been threatened!<br>
<br>

I think I speak for all of us when I say, from now on, please ask for summoned items in a more polite fashion. Here is an example: <br>
 <img src="http://www.furysedge.com/news/030904/quotemod.jpg" style="border:0;" ><br>
